author: HelloFresh
---

Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Put @veggie stock concentrate{1}, 1 cup @water{1%cup}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} in a #small pot{}. Bring to a boil, then add @quinoa{1/2%cup}. Cover, lower heat, and reduce to a simmer. Cook until tender, about ~{15%minutes}.

Wash and dry all produce. Roughly chop @pistachios{1%oz}. Pat @chicken breasts{12%oz} dry with a #paper towel{}, then place on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Evenly spread a thin layer of @dijon mustard{2%tsp} on top of chicken. Press pistachios into mustard. Bake in oven until chicken is no longer pink in center, about ~{20%minutes}.

While chicken cooks, chop @Persian cucumber{1} into small cubes. Halve @grape tomatoes{4%oz}. Chop @mint{1/4%oz} leaves until you have 1 TBSP; set aside 1 tsp for garnish. Halve, peel, and finely dice @shallot{1} until you have 2 TBSP. Zest @lime{1}, then cut into halves. Dice @jalapeño{1}, removing ribs and seeds for less heat.

Combine cucumber, tomatoes, 2 tsp mint, diced shallot, lime zest, a squeeze of lime, jalapeño (to taste), and a drizzle of @olive oil{3%tsp} in a #medium bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

When chicken is cooked through, remove from oven and rest ~{3%minutes} before thinly slicing. Once quinoa is done, fluff with a #fork{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir in a drizzle of @olive oil{} and a drizzle of @sherry vinegar{1%tbsp} (to taste).

Divide quinoa between plates, then top with chicken. Spoon salad on top and garnish with reserved mint.